description:
Ka-Zar, lord of the hidden jungle, is many things. A British nobleman. A man lost in time. A husband. A father. Best friend of a saber-toothed tiger. And younger brother to an incredibly evil man. When the father of Parnival and Kevin Plunder died, he left his sons the very keys to the mysteries of the Savage Land, and Parnival has decided to take the secrets for himself! See Ka-Zar fight for honor and family in the verdant green jungles of the Savage Land and the harsh concrete jungle of New York!

Collecting KA-ZAR (1997) #1-7 & #-1 and material from TALES OF THE MARVEL UNIVERSE #1.
name: Volume One

volume.name: Ka-Zar by Mark Waid & Andy Kubert

description:
The Cat is B(l)ack in her own series and it's international intrigue at its sexiest by Jen Van Meter (Hopeless Savages, JSA) and Javier Pulido (AMAZING SPIDER-MAN). As Spider-Man is stalked during the Grim Hunt, the world's slyest, smartest and sneakiest jewel thief's latest heist puts the Black Cat face-to-face with the family that has been terrorizing Spider-Man's dreams and threatening those closest to him!

Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN PRESENTS: BLACK CAT #1-4 and material from THE MANY LOVES OF THE AMAZING SPIDER-MAN and AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #612.
name: TPB

description: For years, the New Mutants have struggled to hone their powers and teamwork in defense of Charles Xavier's dream of peaceful coexistence between humans and mutants. Now, with the arrival of Cable-a mysterious metal-armed, big-gunned, glowing-eyed man from the future-things will never be same...not for the New Mutants, and not for any mutants! Featuring the threats of Stryfe, Nitro, the Vulture, the Skrulls and Sabretooth! Guest-starring Sunfire and Wolverine! Collecting NEW MUTANTS #86-94 and NEW MUTANTS ANNUAL #5.
name: X-Force: Cable and the New Mutants

After months and months of kung-fu training, Donald Duck has finally become a master...of nothing. But he's not going to let that stop him from striking out on a mission to become Hollywood's latest martial arts movie star! Can the would-be web-footed warrior parlay his acting chopsticks into a life of glitz and glamour? Find out in the final chapter of Feathers of Fury!
name: Return of the Titan of the Tae-Kwon-Duck; A Star is Hatched; Goof-Jitsu

description: Life is once again like a hurricane...here in Duckburg! So you know what that means...DUCKTALES ARE BACK!!! Gear up for adventure as one of the most cherished, fan-favorite Disney franchises explodes back onto the comics page! Join Uncle Scrooge, Donald Duck, Huey, Dewey, Louie and of course Launchpad McQuack as they solve a few mysteries and maybe rewrite some history in action packed adventures never before seen in the US! The Disney Afternoon Revolution is here!
name: Uncle Scrooge: Like a Hurricane

description: The Mad Hatter and Mirror Master team up to drag Batman and The Flash "Through the Looking Glass"! Trapped in a wacky Wonderland filled with white rabbits and Cheshire cats, the heroes have to battle past the pair of villains and a fearsome Jabberwock to find their way back to the real world.
name: Mirror, Mirror...

SHE-HULK Returns In A New Story!
The BEAST!
The POWER Of DOCTOR STRANGE!

description:
A Civil War chapter!

The Heroes for Hire have a new assignment: track Captain America! The heroes want a way to find a way of ending the Civil War peacefully - but one of them is a traitor with a very different plan!

By Justin Gray and Billy Tucci!

Plus: She-Hulk and Two-Gun Kid search New York for the savage Man-Wolf - who also happens to be Shulkie's husband!

By Dan Slott and Rick Burchett.

Also: the Planet Hulk saga explodes as the Hulk and Caiera the Oldstrong lead the rebel forces against the terrifying Spikes!

By Greg Pak and Carlo Pagulayan.
name: Planet Hulk

description:
More Marvel Universe action! The Punisher, Daredevil, Black Widow and Dagger clash with a mythological terror far below New York!

By Chuck Dixon and Ed Barreto.

Also: the Hulk and his new allies begin their war with the Red King's army on the planet Sakaar! Don't miss and epic saga by Greg Pak and Aaron Lopresti.

Plus: a special Christmas tale starring the Silver Surfer, by James Felder and Bryan Hitch.

Also: Mike W. Barr and Frank Miller ask the question: What If Daredevil had become an Agent of SHIELD?
name: The Hulk Goes to War!
The Hulk Versus The Silver Surfer!

description:
More adventures in the Marvel universe!

The Order continue their plans to dominate the world, as Earth's heroes assemble to battle them! Meanwhile, the defenders find themselves trapped in a deadly alien dimension!

By Kurt Busiek, Jo Duff and Ivan Reis.

Also: She-Hulk returns to Bone, Idaho - the town she destroyed in a crazed battle with the Hulk!

By Dan Slott and Scott Kolins.

Plus: Iron man is trapped inside his own armour , and his air's running out! Can Ant-Man help? Classic action by David Michelinie and Jerry Bingham
name: Buried Alive!

description:
100 page special!

Iron Man has found a way to cure Bruce Banner of the Hulk forever - but the Green Goliath ain't going down easily! Get set for an epic scrap between two Marvel powerhouses!

By David Michelinie, Jerry Bingham and Bob Layton.

Also: The Order battles the Avengers - and the Hulk undergoes a strange transformation!

By Kurt Busiek, Jo Duffy, Matt Haley and Dan Jurgens.

Plus: Daredevil returns to tackle the Kingpin!

By Rob Haynes.
name: The Hulk Versus Iron Man!
